    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two!) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottom[s]<strong> </strong>from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray, then scrunch the sides up to create a parcel</p><p>Add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/four-cheese-pizza-with-roasted-tomato-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, remove the tray from the oven and set aside to cool in the tin foil parcel \u2013 these are your <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/four-cheese-pizza-with-roasted-tomato-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tomatoes are roasting, peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the<strong> grated garlic</strong> and 1/3 of your<strong> soft cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!) in a small bowl with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/four-cheese-pizza-with-roasted-tomato-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Grate your<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/four-cheese-pizza-with-roasted-tomato-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add your <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>creamy tomato sauce</strong> between the pizza base[s] and spread it evenly all over with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheddar</strong>, <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and<strong> torn mozzarella</strong></p><p>Dollop the<strong> remaining soft cheese </strong>evenly on top, then sprinkle the <strong>remaining dried oregano</strong> all over</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/four-cheese-pizza-with-roasted-tomato-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the base is crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>four-cheese pizza</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/four-cheese-pizza-with-roasted-tomato-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/four-cheese-pizza-with-roasted-tomato-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> four-cheese pizza</strong> with the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> to the side, then top with the <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong> and drizzle the <strong>tomato juices</strong> all over</p><p>Garnish the pizza with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
